        <div class=3D"droptext">Right now we are in the transition to high =
resolution displays, bringing font rendering
          quality on screen to the realms of print quality. But we're not t=
here yet, and especially on many laptops and
          typical office displays this transition will not be accomplished =
in the foreseeable future. So I wanted the
          glyphs to survive well when squashed into a grid of a few pixels,=
 but still have a level of detail appropriate
          for print and retina displays.
        </div>
      </div>

